<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 1:05AM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Val
Verde County through 145 AM CDT...
At 105 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Juno, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Juno, Bakers Crossing and Devils River State Nat Area Del Norte.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
